  "prompt": "What is mail signature?",
  "response": "A mail signature is a block of text automatically added at the end of an email message. It typically includes:\n\n1. Personal details:\n- Full name\n- Job title\n- Company name\n- Contact information (phone number, email address)\n- Professional credentials\n\n2. Optional additional elements:\n- Company logo\n- Social media links\n- Website URL\n- Legal disclaimers\n- Inspirational quote\n- Professional certification icons\n\n3. Purposes:\n- Provide contact information\n- Establish professional identity\n- Add branding\n- Create a consistent communication style\n- Make communication more personal\n\n4. Common formats:\n- Plain text\n- HTML-formatted\n- Graphical design\n\n5. Where signatures are used:\n- Professional emails\n- Business communications\n- Personal correspondence\n\n6. Creation methods:\n- Email client signature settings\n- Third-party signature generators\n- Manual design and configuration\n\nSignatures help recipients quickly understand who sent the email and how to contact the sender.",
